  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Time to full enteral feeds (hours)</measure>
    <time_frame>week 4 to week 12 daily</time_frame>
    <description>Time to full feeds (hours), defined as time to actual enteral intake of the age-dependent caloric requirements per day (defined as 90 or 120kcal/kg/24h) for at least 24 hours and a concomitant reduction of parenteral fluids to &lt;20ml/kg/24h.&#xD;
The nutrition aim is 120 kcal/kg/24h for premature infants with a birth weight &lt; 1000g or premature infants with a birth weight ≥ 1000g and mother's gestation week at birth before 37+0.&#xD;
The nutrition aim is 90 kcal/kg/24h for born mature infants, mother's gestation week at birth at least 37+0.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
